1
00:00:29,610 --> 00:00:31,870
If only it were me who had been crippled.

2
00:00:32,910 --> 00:00:35,240
Then you wouldn't have ended up like this.

3
00:01:52,140 --> 00:01:53,360
Damn cripple,

4
00:01:53,539 --> 00:01:54,800
are you blind?

5
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,450
Do you even know who I am?

6
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,170
Beat the hell out of him!

7
00:02:06,930 --> 00:02:07,980
You're glaring at me?

8
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:08,520
Yeah.

9
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:16,500
You want some too?

10
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:17,600
Here, have some.

11
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,870
I've got another little treat.

12
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:33,810
Light him up!

13
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,210
Run!

14
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,540
Fun, right?

15
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:42,500
Run!

16
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:46,210
He's getting away.

17
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:58,450
Let's go.

18
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:01,510
Who the hell are you?

19
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:03,070
Trying to play hero, huh?

20
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:04,880
Stop right there!

21
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:16,430
Need a hand?

22
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:20,060
Are you a mute?

23
00:03:21,860 --> 00:03:23,410
I'm talking to you,

24
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,770
damn cripple.

25
00:03:25,210 --> 00:03:26,680
I'm talking to you.

26
00:03:31,130 --> 00:03:32,910
Say something, you cripple!

27
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:41,100
Rip his arm off!

28
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:32,470
[Archives: The Nanyang Mystery]

29
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:35,510
[Episode 17]

30
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:09,470
Shrimpie...

31
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,970
Shrimpie...

32
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:18,330
Shrimpie...

33
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:25,000
Shrimpie...

34
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:30,600
Shrimpie...

35
00:07:48,930 --> 00:07:49,730
Young Master!

36
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:51,560
How can you be out alone
with your legs like this?

37
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,360
Young Master,

38
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:53,880
how did you hurt your hand?

39
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:55,620
Let me push your wheelchair.

40
00:07:58,860 --> 00:07:59,830
Get away from me.

41
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,850
Don't come near me.

42
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:06,980
B-But Young Master, your hand...

43
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,850
What should I do?

44
00:09:51,810 --> 00:09:52,470
What...

45
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,700
What should I do?

46
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,470
Young Master?

47
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,680
Young Master, you're awake.

48
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:48,230
How did you get that injury on your hand?

49
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,100
Yesterday,

50
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:54,480
you came back injured,

51
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,220
and your clothes were all soaked.

52
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:57,270
If Young Master Hailou

53
00:10:57,270 --> 00:10:58,860
finds out you went out on your own,

54
00:10:58,860 --> 00:11:00,120
he'll be worried sick.

55
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,330
Young Master, you're crippled.

56
00:11:11,350 --> 00:11:12,880
You should just stay in bed.

57
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,620
You can't go wandering around on your own.

58
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:15,310
Later,

59
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:17,720
I should tell
Young Master Hailou about this.

60
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,390
Otherwise, when he sees your injury,

61
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,250
he'll blame me.

62
00:11:20,940 --> 00:11:23,320
Just stay in bed since you're crippled.

63
00:11:24,130 --> 00:11:26,730
You get hurt,
and then I have to take care of you.

64
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,200
Shrimpie,

65
00:11:54,870 --> 00:11:55,930
what are you doing?

66
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:28,280
I...

67
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:34,350
What are you doing?

68
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:51,780
It was all a dream...

69
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:28,480
[Puguang Temple]

70
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:54,630
[Almanac]

71
00:13:53,170 --> 00:13:54,620
Young sir,

72
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,940
your aura is a bit stagnant.

73
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:59,500
I'm afraid misfortune may be approaching.

74
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,740
Why don't you let me read your fortune

75
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:04,700
so we may find a way to avert it?

76
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:12,090
You can't even see,

77
00:14:12,410 --> 00:14:14,030
yet you claim my aura is stagnant?

78
00:14:14,030 --> 00:14:15,690
That's a pretty lazy opening.

79
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,720
Although I'm blind,

80
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,500
my heart is not.

81
00:14:21,130 --> 00:14:21,860
Don't worry.

82
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:25,240
I won't charge you a penny if I'm wrong.

83
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,170
Young sir,

84
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:34,150
has something been
weighing on your mind lately?

85
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,290
In life,

86
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:45,220
more often than not,
things don't turn out the way we'd hoped.

87
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:47,100
But from what I can tell,

88
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,390
your trouble

89
00:14:49,820 --> 00:14:51,600
comes from within,

90
00:14:51,670 --> 00:14:53,270
not from anything external.

91
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,960
And this has never

92
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:58,510
happened to you before.

93
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,500
Am I right?

94
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,930
Have you long been afflicted with illness

95
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:28,440
and only recently recovered?

96
00:15:30,770 --> 00:15:33,220
Then can you divine
what it is that has been troubling me?

97
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:34,440
As the saying goes,

98
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:37,500
wisdom is neither imparted lightly
nor sold cheaply.

99
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,580
Young sir, if you're willing to
make a small offering,

100
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:43,150
though I'm no immortal,

101
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,670
perhaps I can try

102
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,000
to unravel what troubles your heart.

103
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:58,270
Since recovering from my illness,

104
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:01,050
I've been haunted over and over again
by a thought

105
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,370
I cannot explain.

106
00:16:07,010 --> 00:16:08,650
I don't want to act on it,

107
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:12,150
but it disturbs my mind,

108
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,410
and I can't suppress it.

109
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:20,060
I don't know if, at this rate,

110
00:16:21,890 --> 00:16:23,550
it'll eventually consume me.

111
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:31,380
And I don't know whether I can destroy it.

112
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,140
From my perspective,

113
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:37,630
you should not fight it.

114
00:16:37,790 --> 00:16:41,270
Follow your heart
and see that thought through.

115
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,890
When you do,
the answer will reveal itself.

116
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:52,370
That's your advice?

117
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,550
Young man, you must know

118
00:16:55,770 --> 00:16:57,530
that fate cannot be defied.

119
00:16:57,550 --> 00:16:58,960
No matter how hard you struggle,

120
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,960
you will eventually walk

121
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,290
the path you are meant to walk.

122
00:17:16,420 --> 00:17:19,480
You said you wouldn't charge
if your reading was wrong.

123
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,460
Well, your reading...

124
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:25,960
