181
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,960
You, Chief.

182
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:13,070
I'm the Chief,

183
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:14,980
and he's the Second Chief.

184
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:16,910
Could the Second Chief be a bad guy?

185
00:21:16,980 --> 00:21:18,780
Let's see who dares slander him.

186
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:22,030
Is it you? Is it you?

187
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:22,740
Is it you?

188
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:26,610
Yuanbao isn't lying.

189
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,740
What he says is true.

190
00:21:27,740 --> 00:21:28,640
He's telling the truth.

191
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:29,440
Believe us.

192
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:30,860
Listen to us.

193
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:32,310
Yuanbao is telling the truth.

194
00:21:32,310 --> 00:21:33,550
Yuanbao isn't lying.

195
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:34,920
He's not lying.

196
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,440
We're telling the truth.

197
00:21:36,460 --> 00:21:38,120
Yuanbao is telling the truth.

198
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:39,660
Yuanbao isn't lying.

199
00:21:39,660 --> 00:21:41,210
Believe us! Believe us!

200
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,770
We're not lying.

201
00:21:42,770 --> 00:21:44,000
What he says is true.

202
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:45,420
Yuanbao...
Yuanbao is really telling the truth.

203
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:46,660
Alright, alright, enough.

204
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:49,310
Looks like this is
another mystery with no clues.

205
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:52,700
How about this? After I'm properly dressed
in my official robes,

206
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,360
I'll settle this case for you.

207
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:55,210
Let's go.

208
00:21:55,570 --> 00:21:56,050
Go in.

209
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,070
Chief!

210
00:21:58,070 --> 00:21:59,220
Wait for me!

211
00:21:59,290 --> 00:21:59,980
Chief!

212
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:01,250
You wanted to kill my cat!

213
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,180
You're a bad guy!

214
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:03,250
You're a bad guy!

215
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,380
Help! Help!

216
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:58,330
Help! Help!

217
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:00,310
Help!

218
00:23:00,380 --> 00:23:01,430
Help!

219
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:04,260
-Wait for me!
-Wait for us!

220
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:05,530
Chief!

221
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:06,920
Help!

222
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,140
Help!

223
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:09,740
-I'll go check it out.
-Help!

224
00:23:11,250 --> 00:23:12,310
Yuanbao!

225
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:13,050
Yuanbao!

226
00:23:13,050 --> 00:23:13,580
Yuanbao!

227
00:23:13,610 --> 00:23:14,210
Shrimpie.

228
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:15,960
What was that?

229
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,540
Why are you hiding there?

230
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:24,530
Bring him back to me.

231
00:23:24,530 --> 00:23:25,050
Okay.

232
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:36,210
Shrimpie.

233
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,680
Stop playing around.

234
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,560
You just play around all day.

235
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:42,070
That's all you do.

236
00:23:42,310 --> 00:23:44,510
Can playing around solve our problems?

237
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:50,200
Fine, I won't play with them anymore.

238
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,860
You've got blood on your nose.

239
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:53,550
I'm fine.

240
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:58,570
Fine? You're fine?

241
00:23:58,810 --> 00:23:59,940
You call this fine?

242
00:23:59,970 --> 00:24:01,500
I said I'm fine, so I am fine.

243
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,750
-Chief!
-Chief!

244
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:09,440
Chief!

245
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:10,980
Yuanbao is crying.

246
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:12,070
Yuanbao is crying.

247
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:12,510
Alright.

248
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:15,180
The Chiefs have
serious matters to discuss.

249
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,550
You guys l-leave first.

250
00:24:17,550 --> 00:24:18,800
Stop playing!

251
00:24:19,610 --> 00:24:21,270
I said, stop playing around with them!

252
00:24:21,270 --> 00:24:22,830
Do you even understand?

253
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:31,420
Avenge Yuanbao!

254
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:32,920
Avenge Yuanbao!

255
00:24:32,980 --> 00:24:34,250
Avenge Yuanbao!

256
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:35,160
Avenge Yuanbao!

257
00:24:35,160 --> 00:24:36,310
Get justice for Yuanbao!

258
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:37,240
Chief!

259
00:24:37,290 --> 00:24:38,830
Avenge Yuanbao!

260
00:24:38,900 --> 00:24:39,510
Stand up for Yuanbao!

261
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:40,350
Listen up,

262
00:24:41,310 --> 00:24:42,480
when the Chiefs

263
00:24:42,510 --> 00:24:43,560
are talking business,

264
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:45,400
don't be chirping away like this,
understand?

265
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,640
Avenge Yuanbao!

266
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:48,220
Avenge Yuanbao!

267
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:49,620
Avenge Yuanbao!

268
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:51,530
Avenge Yuanbao!

269
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:54,050
Avenge Yuanbao!

270
00:24:56,070 --> 00:24:57,330
Avenge Yuanbao!

271
00:24:57,420 --> 00:24:58,850
Avenge Yuanbao!

272
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:00,790
Avenge Yuanbao!

273
00:25:05,350 --> 00:25:06,740
Avenge Yuanbao!

274
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:19,830
The Second Chief is getting angry!

275
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:22,570
Enough. Leave now.

276
00:25:22,670 --> 00:25:26,000
Otherwise, even I won't be able to
protect you, understand?

277
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:30,360
Chief, avenge Yuanbao!

278
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:33,010
Chief, avenge Yuanbao!

279
00:25:33,790 --> 00:25:34,990
What's all the noise?

280
00:25:41,770 --> 00:25:42,240
Mentor.

281
00:25:42,590 --> 00:25:43,350
Meeting.

282
00:25:47,050 --> 00:25:49,740
Chief, please believe us!

283
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:51,100
Chief,

284
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:53,800
didn't you promise to protect us?

285
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:55,020
Chief.

286
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:57,660
Chief, avenge Yuanbao!

287
00:25:57,770 --> 00:25:59,610
Chief, believe us!

288
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:01,720
There are only three of us left
in the Southern Archives.

289
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,740
And you both know

290
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:03,790
who our enemy is.

291
00:26:04,070 --> 00:26:04,790
A few days ago,

292
00:26:04,790 --> 00:26:06,720
the Mo faction warlords
withdrew from Xiacheng.

293
00:26:06,650 --> 00:26:08,630
[Xiacheng News]

294
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:09,170
The consulate is negotiating with
the government.

295
00:26:09,170 --> 00:26:11,290
Due to the deaths of Warner and his group,

296
00:26:11,290 --> 00:26:13,580
[Should the Mo faction
bear responsibility?]

297
00:26:11,550 --> 00:26:13,970
they're holding
the Beilian warlord Mo Yungao accountable—

298
00:26:13,970 --> 00:26:17,030
the man responsible for
the slaughter of the Archives.

299
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:18,310
The situation is volatile now.

300
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:20,160
The government's word isn't worth a damn.

301
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:21,310
What's the use of
demanding accountability?

302
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:22,190
Where is he?

303
00:26:24,010 --> 00:26:25,070
Going after him...

304
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,810
won't be easy.

305
00:26:29,770 --> 00:26:31,400
That was before his promotion.

306
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,530
In just a few months,

307
00:26:32,550 --> 00:26:34,050
he rose to division commander

308
00:26:34,050 --> 00:26:36,030
and quickly took control
of all of Beilian.

309
00:26:36,030 --> 00:26:37,610
He's not like ordinary warlords.

310
00:26:37,610 --> 00:26:39,610
Officially, he answers to
the coalition military government,

311
00:26:39,610 --> 00:26:40,470
but in reality,

312
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,320
he rules independently.

313
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,750
His relationship with the government
is complicated.

314
00:26:44,750 --> 00:26:46,350
So the government prefers to

315
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:47,500
placate him

316
00:26:48,330 --> 00:26:50,260
rather than provoke him directly.

317
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:54,000
On top of that, he has many skilled fighters
around him at all times.

318
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,440
You won't be able to get close to him.

319
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:56,360
I get it.

320
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:58,400
Mo Yungao is basically a local kingpin

321
00:26:58,400 --> 00:26:59,660
with enormous power.

322
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,050
So what?

323
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:03,680
Does he have soldiers guarding him

324
00:27:03,770 --> 00:27:05,830
even when he eats, sleeps, and shits?

325
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:07,920
To take him out,

326
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,850
we first need to
figure out his whereabouts

327
00:27:09,850 --> 00:27:11,140
and his plan.

328
00:27:11,980 --> 00:27:12,550
Haixia.

329
00:27:14,750 --> 00:27:16,810
This is a secret letter I memorized

330
00:27:16,940 --> 00:27:18,940
while I was being hunted on the ship.

331
00:27:24,030 --> 00:27:24,590
Hold on.

332
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,350
When did you two
have a meeting on that ship

333
00:27:27,350 --> 00:27:28,460
and leave me out of it?

334
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:29,850
It wasn't on the ship.

335
00:27:30,220 --> 00:27:31,620
It was before you woke up.

336
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,600
He told me everything he discovered there.

337
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:45,680
"If the Pitcher Plant Project succeeds,

338
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:47,160
[Nanling] [Chuhan]
[Guangchuan] [Changxiang]

339
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:48,380
and all Archives personnel are eliminated,

340
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,200
proceed immediately to the next phase.

341
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:52,860
This is

342
00:27:54,090 --> 00:27:55,530
20 years of my life's work.

343
00:27:55,530 --> 00:27:56,530
It must not fail."

344
00:27:57,850 --> 00:27:58,710
So Mo Yungao

345
00:27:58,740 --> 00:28:00,470
will keep stirring up trouble?

346
00:28:00,510 --> 00:28:01,530
My deduction is

347
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:03,790
that Mo Yungao has encrypted his plan,

348
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:06,540
and these four illustrations
are the cipher.

349
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:08,270
The codebook is an ancient prophecy text

350
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:09,930
called "Hongmeng Prophecy."

351
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,890
I knew the Archives had the original copy,

352
00:28:15,700 --> 00:28:18,100
and I was the only one
who could retrieve it.

353
00:28:20,180 --> 00:28:22,110
That's why I couldn't die back then

354
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:23,770
and chose to...

355
00:28:25,460 --> 00:28:26,260
fake my death.

356
00:28:37,220 --> 00:28:38,880
But I was also taking a gamble,

357
00:28:39,610 --> 00:28:41,670
betting on whether you could save me.

358
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:49,340
Fortunately, I won that bet.

359
00:28:57,310 --> 00:28:59,220
So why are you the only one
who can get that book?

360
00:28:59,220 --> 00:29:01,160
Some of the Archives'
most valuable evidence

361
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:04,250
is stored inside mechanical lockboxes.

362
00:29:04,350 --> 00:29:06,500
If someone opens one incorrectly
or tries to force it open,

363
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:07,350
the acid sealed inside

364
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:09,270
will dissolve all the evidence

365
00:29:09,420 --> 00:29:10,900
to prevent it from leaking.

366
00:29:10,900 --> 00:29:12,230
In the entire Archives,

367
00:29:12,460 --> 00:29:13,450
he's the only one

368
00:29:14,050 --> 00:29:15,450
capable of opening them.

369
00:30:23,500 --> 00:30:24,630
Can you decipher it?

370
00:30:30,390 --> 00:30:31,530
[Nanling] [Chuhan]
[Guangchuan] [Changxiang]

371
00:30:42,170 --> 00:30:44,460
[Moon]

372
00:30:52,710 --> 00:30:53,550
[Ancient Capital] [Nanling]

373
00:30:53,570 --> 00:30:54,340
[Nine Curves] [Dragon's Roar]

374
00:30:54,370 --> 00:30:55,210
[Hundred Cranes] [Lonely Moon]

375
00:30:55,250 --> 00:30:56,810
[Nanling] [Chuhan]
[Guangchuan] [Changxiang]

376
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,190
[Nanling]

377
00:31:05,540 --> 00:31:08,620
[Detailed Coastal Topography Map]

378
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:06,400
Nanling,

379
00:31:06,530 --> 00:31:07,380
Chuhan,

380
00:31:07,570 --> 00:31:08,300
Guangchuan,

381
00:31:08,310 --> 00:31:09,200
Changxiang...

382
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,310
These are the villages

383
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:35,840
where the Twilight Grass poison outbreak
occurred in Nanyang.

384
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:41,750
Connected in chronological order...

385
00:31:41,580 --> 00:31:45,840
[Xucheng] [Jilanna]

386
00:31:46,310 --> 00:31:47,170
they lead here.

387
00:31:53,170 --> 00:31:55,220
[Nanling] [Chuhan]
[Guangchuan] [Changxiang]

388
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:55,550
So the Twilight Grass incident in Nanyang

389
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,250
[Xucheng] [Jilanna]

390
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:56,810
was merely a trial run.

391
00:31:58,350 --> 00:31:59,060
Looks like

392
00:31:59,180 --> 00:32:01,630
he's ready to do it for real
on the mainland now.

393
00:32:01,630 --> 00:32:02,940
We must stop him.

394
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:06,290
It's just that...

395
00:32:06,290 --> 00:32:08,790
We have no way to predict
when he'll make his move.

396
00:32:08,790 --> 00:32:11,030
The Mo faction has suffered
such heavy losses,

397
00:32:11,030 --> 00:32:12,170
so they probably can't act anytime soon.

398
00:32:12,170 --> 00:32:13,350
Facing a well-armed army

399
00:32:13,350 --> 00:32:15,240
of this size...

400
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:20,420
the three of us alone
have little chance of wiping them out.

401
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:25,510
Mentor,

402
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,480
our Zhang family is so powerful.

403
00:32:28,570 --> 00:32:30,640
Now that our Southern Archives
has been taken out,

404
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:31,920
won't the Western, Northern,

405
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:33,200
and Eastern branches

406
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:35,110
send reinforcements to help us?

407
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:36,680
We can't count on them.

408
00:32:45,610 --> 00:32:46,670
They're no help,

409
00:32:47,010 --> 00:32:48,210
but we still have you.

410
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:51,270
Mentor, what are your thoughts now?

411
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:53,400
To bring down Mo Yungao

412
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,540
and rebuild the Archives, of course.

413
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:01,750
Mentor,

414
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:04,480
you've already got a plan, don't you?

415
00:33:08,300 --> 00:33:10,880
We'll go to Changxiang
to seek help from someone.

416
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:12,720
He should know about Mo Yungao.

417
00:33:13,510 --> 00:33:16,050
He may be able to help us track him down

418
00:33:16,180 --> 00:33:17,640
and lend us some manpower.

419
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:18,980
Who?

420
00:33:19,570 --> 00:33:20,700
We're short on time.

421
00:33:20,790 --> 00:33:22,120
I'll explain on the way.

422
00:33:22,720 --> 00:33:23,680
Zhang Haixia,

423
00:33:23,830 --> 00:33:25,140
you won't be traveling with us.

424
00:33:25,140 --> 00:33:26,270
You'll leave first.

425
00:33:26,700 --> 00:33:27,380
Mentor,

426
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:29,180
I'll go with Shrimpie.

427
00:33:29,420 --> 00:33:31,150
I can take care of him on the way.

428
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:33,870
This trip to Changxiang is very dangerous.

429
00:33:34,070 --> 00:33:35,360
I need you with me.

430
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,290
I have other plans for him.

431
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:39,350
I'll have someone I trust escort you.

432
00:33:44,350 --> 00:33:46,750
-No matter how reliable they are...
-Okay.

433
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:48,330
In that case,

434
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:50,400
tomorrow morning...

435
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,970
we will set off separately.

436
00:34:27,030 --> 00:34:28,230
You can feel them now?

437
00:34:29,590 --> 00:34:31,590
That means you're recovering well.

438
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:33,370
It's been three years.

439
00:34:33,500 --> 00:34:34,429
How does it feel?

440
00:34:37,570 --> 00:34:38,699
Not much, I suppose.

441
00:34:40,510 --> 00:34:42,909
Isn't there still a chance
I'll get better?

442
00:34:45,330 --> 00:34:47,460
You've been this way since childhood,

443
00:34:47,530 --> 00:34:49,670
always keeping
everything bottled up inside.

444
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:52,670
You need to think about yourself too,
not just others.

445
00:34:52,730 --> 00:34:53,190
Come on.

446
00:34:53,900 --> 00:34:55,370
I was raised by you.

447
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:58,450
Aren't you the same?

448
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:00,230
No.

449
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:07,460
Is it because I don't have much time left?

450
00:35:12,130 --> 00:35:14,250
Mentor, you told me

451
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,580
that the fake-death drug
is actually a poison—

452
00:35:17,580 --> 00:35:19,040
that it only delays death,

453
00:35:19,530 --> 00:35:21,590
and in the end, the person still dies.

454
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,300
How will I die?

455
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:36,410
The fake-death drug
actually comes in two doses.

456
00:35:37,860 --> 00:35:40,520
The first dose is the poison
you took on the ship,

457
00:35:40,920 --> 00:35:43,050
which put you into a death-like state.

458
00:35:45,470 --> 00:35:47,270
The second dose is also a poison—

459
00:35:47,650 --> 00:35:49,310
fighting poison with poison.

460
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,420
It can wake you up,

461
00:35:52,010 --> 00:35:53,780
but it also affects the brain.

462
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:57,710
I originally didn't want to
give you the second dose.

463
00:36:01,170 --> 00:36:03,430
The first agent who ever used that poison

464
00:36:04,880 --> 00:36:06,480
began losing control

465
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:09,100
not long after being revived.

466
00:36:09,670 --> 00:36:12,270
He became extremely
agitated and aggressive.

467
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:14,030
During an assignment,

468
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:16,010
he slaughtered an entire village

469
00:36:17,030 --> 00:36:18,230
without any warning,

470
00:36:19,260 --> 00:36:20,860
and no one could control him.

471
00:36:22,260 --> 00:36:23,000
So...

472
00:36:26,050 --> 00:36:27,980
everyone who has ever used the drug

473
00:36:28,640 --> 00:36:30,970
has ultimately been killed by my own hand.

474
00:36:37,380 --> 00:36:38,130
Mentor...

475
00:36:42,460 --> 00:36:43,780
Will you kill me too?
